# Interview Questions

## What is the difference between docker run and docker start?

docker run creates a new container from an image and starts it.

docker start starts an existing stopped container.

---

## What is the difference between docker start and docker exec?

docker start only starts the container.

docker exec opens an interactive terminal inside a running container.

---

## What happens when we type exit after docker exec?

Only the Bash shell closes.

The container continues running.

---

## What happens when we type exit after docker run -it?

The main process exits.

The container stops.

---

## What is docker logs?

docker logs displays the stdout and stderr output generated by the main application running inside a container. It is mainly used for troubleshooting and debugging.

---

## What is docker cp?

docker cp copies files and directories between the host machine and a Docker container.

---

# Key Takeaways

✔ docker run creates a new container.

✔ docker start starts an existing stopped container.

✔ docker stop stops a running container.

✔ docker restart = docker stop + docker start.

✔ docker exec opens a shell inside a running container.

✔ Exiting docker exec does NOT stop the container.

✔ docker logs is the first command used to troubleshoot containerized applications.

✔ docker cp copies files between host and container in both directions.

